MBOMBELA – According to spokesman for the Department of Community Safety, Security and Liaison, Joseph Mabuza, the accident occurred at the traffic lights at the Sasol filling station in Rocky Drift at 18:30. He said it was suspected that it was a head-on collision, but it was still being investigated. No more details about the crash could be confirmed at the time of publication. The man was taken to hospital. Mabuza said he was in a critical condition. ALSO SEE: Head-on collision claim six  ALSO READ: Horrific R40 accident leaves four dead